meta.description: United Airlines United Club (Gate C17) at Washington Dulles International Airport (IAD), Concourse C. Learn more about the lounge: amenities, photos, review, opening hours, location.

lounge.name: United Airlines United Club (Gate C17)
lounge.description: United Club locations offer a wide range of amenities to make your experience productive and enjoyable. Relax in a sophisticated environment when you wait for your flight in the United Club.

reviews.content: It’s not terrible. Spacious and there are outlets at nearly every seat, but it’s in the basement and breakfast options are subpar. If I had more time I’d just walk to the Turkish Lounge near B41.
I spend a lot of time in United lounges. As many times as I have been in this one, it’s usually cheese and salad bar. I do like the selection of mixed drinks and the bar tenders are always friendly.
I usually stop here for the toilets only and then leave. Climate control on top floor not functioning properly. Cheese cubes and celery sticks for $550/year.
They do not allow active military unless in uniform or R&R.
This is a very solid United Club. It can get crowded at times, but overall, it is very comfortable. Decent food options along with friendly workers made for an A+ experience.
Limited food options no matter what meal.
This lounge denied me even if I was eligible as same-day armed forces active duty traveler. Very disappointed.
Recently updated, with a lot more added outlets and new furniture. Restrooms could still use an update, but the lounge is nice. Good bar, good snacks, good outlets, and good furniture.
Recently updated with new furniture, this lounge is nice for an older United lounge.
This is a solid lounge - not great, but dependable. It is quiet and the staff is extraordinarily helpful.
Basic UA lounge with the usual UA snacks and drinks. Nothing fancy.
Pretty basic but good for United Clubs.
Functional lounge, better than Air France lounge, not as good as Lufthansa. Disappointing that membership will no longer permit access when not flying Star. No longer a point in having membership.
This is just a typical below-average domestic lounge.
Nothing really special. The fridge had warm sodas in it. There were minimal snacks and it was 25 minute walk from my gate.
Nice lounge by United standards. Spacious, quiet, and clean. Design was nice.
Blazing fast wifi. ~24download, 47upload!
Nice renovations have been done. Would be nice to have more snack selections.
Bartender was on her cellphone while serving people. Carrots crackers and cheese, can't get lower than that. Few free drinks offering otherwise, pay for yourself. Only reason to come in is wifi.
Nice lounge. Admitted because I am active duty military and had orders. Good service, lots of snacks/soda. All chairs, no sofas. At least 4 outlets at every seat, lots of cubicles. Thank you United!
Usual United Club with minimal offerings. If you have a choice then go to the club closest to your gate as all are equally as busy.
This lounge is similar to all the United Clubs that I've been to. Limited and crowded seating. Food is limited to crackers and cookies. Power outlets are sparse and staff is indifferent.
This lounge could be better: there's a scarcity of outlets, food and drinks.
This lounge is great, and has a quiet upper level. The Herman Miller Aeron chairs in the business center are a great touch.
